00:18:25.520 --> 00:18:29.838
and I wanted to actually
live this kind of philosophy.

00:18:29.838 --> 00:18:35.140
So at that time, also, one thing
was that, in social sector,

00:18:35.140 --> 00:18:38.540
lots of things called
for a very high degree

00:18:38.540 --> 00:18:39.735
of technical expertise.

00:18:39.735 --> 00:18:43.616
They were domains like working
with farmers in downtrodden

00:18:43.616 --> 00:18:47.560
areas , or environmental
issues, or many such things.

00:18:47.560 --> 00:18:49.000
And I didn't have
any such thing.

00:18:49.000 --> 00:18:51.230
So I asked myself,
then, what do I have?

00:18:51.230 --> 00:18:55.610
I don't have any technical
expertise of such domains.

00:18:55.610 --> 00:19:00.310
So I just thought that basic
human emotions, which are very,

00:19:00.310 --> 00:19:02.411
very universal-- love and care.

00:19:02.411 --> 00:19:04.410
So these basics [INAUDIBLE],
and I thought that,

00:19:04.410 --> 00:19:07.050
let me start the work,
which is a manifestation

00:19:07.050 --> 00:19:09.340
of these basic human values.

00:19:09.340 --> 00:19:13.680
So my work did not start
with any cerebral motivation

00:19:13.680 --> 00:19:14.710
or intellectual ideas.

00:19:14.710 --> 00:19:16.370
There was no grand
idea involved.

00:19:16.370 --> 00:19:19.930
I mean, I always say that
the most simple thing,

00:19:19.930 --> 00:19:23.120
really speaking what
we have been doing.

00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:28.540
Even an unlettered woman in
the most remote area in India

00:19:28.540 --> 00:19:33.560
may be bringing up her children
with her utmost care and love.

00:19:33.560 --> 00:19:37.760
So the idea was to manifest
these values, this sentiment.

00:19:37.760 --> 00:19:39.810
So the whole organization
built on that spirit.

00:19:39.810 --> 00:19:42.080
So all the processes which
happen at the organization

00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:42.850
got built up.

00:19:42.850 --> 00:19:47.020
They bore the stamp of
these guiding sentiments

00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:49.240
of loving caring.

00:19:49.240 --> 00:19:58.082
Now, so this is our mission--
changing lives permanently

00:19:58.082 --> 00:20:00.560
of such children, homeless,
family-less children, highly

00:20:00.560 --> 00:20:05.430
vulnerable children, so children
from backgrounds like orphans,

00:20:05.430 --> 00:20:09.520
street children, girl children
from mass prostitution areas,

00:20:09.520 --> 00:20:13.360
whose mothers are already--
They were victimized

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:16.550
at some point in time and
starting fresh in prostitution.

00:20:16.550 --> 00:20:18.480
And they, themselves,
are very vulnerable

00:20:18.480 --> 00:20:20.845
to being pushed into that
thing, because there's

00:20:20.845 --> 00:20:23.056
a very high degree of
generation-to-generation

00:20:23.056 --> 00:20:27.390
continuity in prostitution,
organized prostitution.

00:20:27.390 --> 00:20:29.510
So these were our domains.

00:20:29.510 --> 00:20:32.890
And then later on, from very
impoverished tribal areas,

00:20:32.890 --> 00:20:35.430
particularly those
which were affected

00:20:35.430 --> 00:20:40.350
by the Naxal movement of extreme
left-wing, violent movements.

00:20:40.350 --> 00:20:44.600
There are pockets in
[INAUDIBLE] in eastern India.

00:20:44.600 --> 00:20:47.090
So this was the thing.

00:20:47.090 --> 00:20:51.120
So in three children just
in a rented building,

00:20:51.120 --> 00:20:52.940
I did not have any funds.

00:20:52.940 --> 00:20:55.920
I did not look for any kind of
funding support, formal funding

00:20:55.920 --> 00:20:56.420
support.

00:20:56.420 --> 00:20:58.440
I just started in my own way.

00:20:58.440 --> 00:21:03.140
I did not have a job, because
I did not take up a job.

00:21:03.140 --> 00:21:06.410
But some part-time,
I used to give

00:21:06.410 --> 00:21:09.630
for just earning that
much, which could start,

00:21:09.630 --> 00:21:11.410
which would help
me in starting this

00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:13.930
and in this way, in a
rented building with friends

00:21:13.930 --> 00:21:16.320
supporting, in that manner.

00:21:16.320 --> 00:21:21.370
So actually, a huge degree
of individual support,

00:21:21.370 --> 00:21:25.230
actually 75%, 80% of support
is through individuals.

00:21:25.230 --> 00:21:31.630
And only I guess 20% through
institutional donors like, say,

00:21:31.630 --> 00:21:35.050
corporates or funding
agencies, et cetera.

00:21:35.050 --> 00:21:38.050
I always believed that
all the work in the world

00:21:38.050 --> 00:21:39.340
is done by individuals.

00:21:39.340 --> 00:21:43.470
So I always had a huge faith
in individual goodness.

00:21:43.470 --> 00:21:45.610
Even institutional
support that we get

00:21:45.610 --> 00:21:48.710
is as a result of championing
or some individual supporter

00:21:48.710 --> 00:21:51.230
with internalized vision.

00:21:51.230 --> 00:21:53.980
So that approach and
belief continues.

00:21:53.980 --> 00:21:57.890
In this way, from tutoring
three all these years

00:21:57.890 --> 00:22:00.090
are-- the residential
institution

00:22:00.090 --> 00:22:01.269
has come up in this way.

00:22:01.269 --> 00:22:02.810
And in next three
years, actually, we

00:22:02.810 --> 00:22:06.400
are going for a
faster scaling now

00:22:06.400 --> 00:22:10.020
that our processes are
all set, and leadership

00:22:10.020 --> 00:22:11.890
at many different levels.

00:22:11.890 --> 00:22:14.950
Operationally speaking,
Parivaar is now on an autopilot.

00:22:14.950 --> 00:22:17.860
So even my involvement,
operationally speaking,

00:22:17.860 --> 00:22:21.070
is not required to that extent.

00:22:21.070 --> 00:22:23.910
So all other tiers of
leadership and management

00:22:23.910 --> 00:22:24.680
have been created.

00:22:24.680 --> 00:22:28.440
So we are looking for
a faster expansion

00:22:28.440 --> 00:22:31.760
in the next few years, because
need for such a service

00:22:31.760 --> 00:22:36.290
is huge in India.

00:22:36.290 --> 00:22:41.300
Now, this is basically like
West Bengal and Jharkhand.

00:22:41.300 --> 00:22:44.290
These are the primary bases
from where we have children.

00:22:44.290 --> 00:22:47.660
We created our field networks
in these 14, 15 districts

00:22:47.660 --> 00:22:49.870
and some other pockets in
neighboring states-- Bihar,

00:22:49.870 --> 00:22:52.669
[INAUDIBLE], Chhattisgarh.

00:22:52.669 --> 00:22:53.710
Statewise it's like this.

00:22:53.710 --> 00:22:56.280
So immediate portion
is from West Bengal

00:22:56.280 --> 00:22:59.880
and then some tribal
districts in Jharkhand,

00:22:59.880 --> 00:23:01.535
impoverished districts.

00:23:04.271 --> 00:23:07.130
Now, like the film
also mentioned,

00:23:07.130 --> 00:23:09.750
so we screen a
large number of kids

00:23:09.750 --> 00:23:12.770
which are brought to our
notice through diverse facets,

00:23:12.770 --> 00:23:16.426
through field groups, local
NGOs, local self-government

00:23:16.426 --> 00:23:20.080
like, say, panchayats,
or municipal authorities,

00:23:20.080 --> 00:23:24.640
or government department of,
say, child welfare or police.

00:23:24.640 --> 00:23:28.550
So all these, actually,
are primary referees

00:23:28.550 --> 00:23:32.160
of cases and upon which
we do a very detailed site

00:23:32.160 --> 00:23:37.450
visit and a neediness analysis
because our capacity of intake

00:23:37.450 --> 00:23:39.250
at any point in time is limited.

00:23:39.250 --> 00:23:42.320
And the cases which come to our
attention far outnumber that,

00:23:42.320 --> 00:23:45.930
so it's really on the
basis of neediness.

00:23:45.930 --> 00:23:48.120
And at the same
time, we also try

00:23:48.120 --> 00:23:53.220
to assess that there are no
chance of dropout in that case.

00:23:53.220 --> 00:23:57.430
So we just ensure during
our pre-admission exercise

00:23:57.430 --> 00:24:00.420
and dialogue with the
referring party-- it could

00:24:00.420 --> 00:24:03.640
be the relative or folks of
the village of the child--

00:24:03.640 --> 00:24:05.500
that how desperate
and motivated they

00:24:05.500 --> 00:24:09.320
are to see the child
into such a system

00:24:09.320 --> 00:24:10.540
of long-term transformation.

00:24:10.540 --> 00:24:13.090
So very often, I am
asked this question

00:24:13.090 --> 00:24:15.910
of how do you motivate
the folks of the child,

00:24:15.910 --> 00:24:17.800
and I answer it in this
way-- that we do not

00:24:17.800 --> 00:24:19.220
have to motivate.

00:24:19.220 --> 00:24:21.440
They have to motivate
us how desperately they

00:24:21.440 --> 00:24:24.800
need such a service, because
another demand of such

00:24:24.800 --> 00:24:26.570
is service is anyway huge.

00:24:26.570 --> 00:24:29.530
And so neediness and,
at the same time,

00:24:29.530 --> 00:24:33.030
minimal chance of
dropout from the program

00:24:33.030 --> 00:24:35.530
these are our main
criteria while

00:24:35.530 --> 00:24:38.350
short-listing for
admitting into Parivaar.

00:24:38.350 --> 00:24:43.900
So children are admitted
during the age of 4 to 10.

00:24:43.900 --> 00:24:45.080
That's the entry point.

00:24:45.080 --> 00:24:47.750
And when, in case
of siblings, we

00:24:47.750 --> 00:24:51.560
take all the siblings so that
the family bonding continues.

00:24:51.560 --> 00:24:53.610
So you have a large
number of sets

00:24:53.610 --> 00:24:59.190
of siblings, four brothers and
sisters, or three, like that.

00:24:59.190 --> 00:25:01.830
So all of them,
together, progress.

00:25:01.830 --> 00:25:04.440
And there is a
considerable degree

00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:07.630
of rootedness with
their background,

00:25:07.630 --> 00:25:11.564
like through our own field
visits to their areas,

00:25:11.564 --> 00:25:14.720
or we invite
periodically [INAUDIBLE],

00:25:14.720 --> 00:25:16.210
all the arrangements.

00:25:16.210 --> 00:25:21.290
So from far-off places, 300,
400 miles, the relatives

00:25:21.290 --> 00:25:25.010
or religious continue
to come to Parivaar.

00:25:25.010 --> 00:25:27.920
So that ensures that
the children also

00:25:27.920 --> 00:25:31.110
have the rootedness
with their earlier

00:25:31.110 --> 00:25:32.430
community or background.

00:25:32.430 --> 00:25:33.690
That remains intact.

00:25:33.690 --> 00:25:36.670
So this also, I'm
very often asked,

00:25:36.670 --> 00:25:41.510
that such a-- since there is
a very, very drastic shift,

00:25:41.510 --> 00:25:44.370
so how do the children
themselves adjust to this?

00:25:44.370 --> 00:25:48.315
But my experience has been
that they themselves take it

00:25:48.315 --> 00:25:49.670
in a very, very positive way.

00:25:49.670 --> 00:25:53.200
So rather than de-rooting
from their past,

00:25:53.200 --> 00:25:55.650
it's actually an
enhanced motivation

00:25:55.650 --> 00:25:59.160
to do-- conclude something,
give back, and actually impact

00:25:59.160 --> 00:26:01.130
their own local
communities, once they

00:26:01.130 --> 00:26:02.850
are in a position to do so.

00:26:02.850 --> 00:26:05.880
So it's like this.

00:26:05.880 --> 00:26:09.520
So education-wise,
also, younger children--

00:26:09.520 --> 00:26:11.650
those who do not have a
backlog, who are, say,

00:26:11.650 --> 00:26:16.210
like around five or six-- they
start with the earlier grades.

00:26:16.210 --> 00:26:18.140
And those who are
slightly older, say,

00:26:18.140 --> 00:26:21.600
8, 9, 10, almost
everyone at Parivaar

00:26:21.600 --> 00:26:25.086
is without any
exposure to education.

00:26:25.086 --> 00:26:27.660
So such children, who have a
huge backlog in terms of age,

00:26:27.660 --> 00:26:30.530
they are taken through fast
learning bridging program

00:26:30.530 --> 00:26:34.210
and then admitted to a
grade on par with their age.

00:26:34.210 --> 00:26:36.580
So this is like our own school.

00:26:36.580 --> 00:26:39.820
And after that, under
our care, only children

00:26:39.820 --> 00:26:41.770
continue to-- like
just from a family,

00:26:41.770 --> 00:26:44.850
how kids at an
outside institution.

00:26:44.850 --> 00:26:46.260
So after, they are living.

00:26:46.260 --> 00:26:49.700
Since teams become very
diverse, some kids actually

00:26:49.700 --> 00:26:51.970
go for sciences,
some after that,

00:26:51.970 --> 00:26:53.200
into engineering, computer.

00:26:53.200 --> 00:26:55.930
We have kids in computer
science, engineering,

00:26:55.930 --> 00:27:00.041
and, say, nursing, or it could
be other medical or some skill

00:27:00.041 --> 00:27:01.040
in a vocational program.

00:27:01.040 --> 00:27:03.800
We have a large-scale
vocational program also

00:27:03.800 --> 00:27:09.160
for children who are
academically not that bright,

00:27:09.160 --> 00:27:13.360
but that also ensures
a career, which

00:27:13.360 --> 00:27:15.640
also has an upward
mobility possibility

00:27:15.640 --> 00:27:17.180
through skilled programs.

00:27:17.180 --> 00:27:20.580
In India these days, actually,
a huge amount of thing

00:27:20.580 --> 00:27:22.550
is being done in the
skill space, which was not

00:27:22.550 --> 00:27:23.860
the case a few years back.

00:27:23.860 --> 00:27:27.370
That was a tremendous-- it
was a macro-level change,

00:27:27.370 --> 00:27:28.930
and we are also getting benefit.

00:27:28.930 --> 00:27:32.580
A few years back, I also
used to anxiety about this,

00:27:32.580 --> 00:27:36.860
like about what about the
kids who are not doing well

00:27:36.860 --> 00:27:39.530
academically or who have,
say, some kind of learning

00:27:39.530 --> 00:27:42.420
disability or slow learners.

00:27:42.420 --> 00:27:46.930
But a huge amount of vibrancy
is there in the last few years

00:27:46.930 --> 00:27:49.550
at the national skill level
and corporation coming

00:27:49.550 --> 00:27:53.390
and lots of courses in
blue collar space, which

00:27:53.390 --> 00:27:58.030
ensures a sure placement and
placement in organized sector.

00:27:58.030 --> 00:28:00.150
Earlier the skills space
was very disorganized.

00:28:00.150 --> 00:28:03.360
It's becoming increasingly
more organized now.

00:28:03.360 --> 00:28:05.660
So that's a good thing,
nationally speaking.

00:28:05.660 --> 00:28:09.040
So these are also
supplementary-- we

00:28:09.040 --> 00:28:14.330
have a lot of supplementary
support to education

00:28:14.330 --> 00:28:17.510
so that children to do well,
just like how in a family

00:28:17.510 --> 00:28:19.410
all the processes which
are there in a family

00:28:19.410 --> 00:28:22.360
are in some form
replicated at our end.

00:28:22.360 --> 00:28:26.230
So just like in a family, how
parents or older siblings would

00:28:26.230 --> 00:28:28.430
guide, or tutor,
or mentor the kids,

00:28:28.430 --> 00:28:33.100
we have our own
systems of doing that.

00:28:33.100 --> 00:28:36.820
So it's basically right from,
you could say, KG to PG,

00:28:36.820 --> 00:28:39.100
also secondary out
into [INAUDIBLE]

00:28:39.100 --> 00:28:44.780
graduation handholding,
and through a placement.

00:28:44.780 --> 00:28:48.680
And actually, even after that,
they need a lot of support.

00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:51.850
Like our kids, earliest kids,
are now getting into jobs.

00:28:51.850 --> 00:28:53.920
So suppose they are in a city.

00:28:53.920 --> 00:28:56.050
They have got a job
in Kolkata city.

00:28:56.050 --> 00:28:57.960
So we have to ensure
that we do this stay.

00:28:57.960 --> 00:29:00.649
And initially maybe one
year, one and a half year,

00:29:00.649 --> 00:29:01.690
all that kind of support.

00:29:01.690 --> 00:29:03.750
Maybe they have to take
a rental condition.

00:29:03.750 --> 00:29:06.400
They have to give a deposit
for that, and all that.

00:29:06.400 --> 00:29:09.247
So it's just like
having-- until they

00:29:09.247 --> 00:29:11.590
are completely on their own.

00:29:11.590 --> 00:29:14.680
So it's like how a
family would support.

00:29:14.680 --> 00:29:20.960
Parivaar is actually a family
in the garb of an institution.

00:29:20.960 --> 00:29:25.176
So skills and vocational are
something which I talked about.

00:29:25.176 --> 00:29:29.880
So a number of courses, say,
hardware, computer hardware,

00:29:29.880 --> 00:29:35.440
networking, electronics,
consumer goods servicing,

00:29:35.440 --> 00:29:40.460
beautician, BPO, hotel
manager and hospitality,

00:29:40.460 --> 00:29:43.590
a number of huge area
of such skilled programs

00:29:43.590 --> 00:29:47.830
we run in collaboration also
with some specialist agencies,

00:29:47.830 --> 00:29:52.910
which are doing that and which
ensure a placement after that,

00:29:52.910 --> 00:29:55.380
guaranteed placement.

00:29:55.380 --> 00:29:58.740
Now, in all of this, this
is the most important aspect

00:29:58.740 --> 00:30:01.630
of Parivaar, even more
important than the education,

00:30:01.630 --> 00:30:06.080
because in a residential
center, but in a family,

00:30:06.080 --> 00:30:08.480
as you can imagine, many
of you will be parents.

00:30:08.480 --> 00:30:11.605
So the responsibility
of parenting

00:30:11.605 --> 00:30:13.430
and the same
responsibility we have.

00:30:13.430 --> 00:30:17.550
So on health issues,
on overall care-taking.

00:30:17.550 --> 00:30:22.670
So we have [INAUDIBLE]
system and very personalized.

00:30:22.670 --> 00:30:25.640
So lots of children, when
they come to Parivaar,

00:30:25.640 --> 00:30:29.470
they have huge malnourishment,
and supplements

00:30:29.470 --> 00:30:30.600
have to be given to them.

00:30:30.600 --> 00:30:33.960
So it's very, very
individualized.

00:30:33.960 --> 00:30:36.000
Individualized health
charts are there.

00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:38.340
Medical files are
there for all children.

00:30:38.340 --> 00:30:40.462
Visual medical
histories are there

00:30:40.462 --> 00:30:43.030
right from the time
they enter Parivaar.

00:30:43.030 --> 00:30:47.300
We have a medical staff,
resident medical staff,

00:30:47.300 --> 00:30:50.373
comprising nurses, paramedical
staff, et cetera, ambulances,

00:30:50.373 --> 00:30:53.454
and everything,
arrangements with hospitals,

00:30:53.454 --> 00:30:56.710
tie-ups with hospitals,
group insurance

00:30:56.710 --> 00:30:59.670
for the whole children, so
all those kinds of things.

00:30:59.670 --> 00:31:04.170
These are developments things,
which the film also depicted.

00:31:04.170 --> 00:31:07.770
So I think the like
the immediate success

00:31:07.770 --> 00:31:11.040
point of Parivaar is,
actually, ensuring

00:31:11.040 --> 00:31:12.660
that there is a
really high degree

00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:16.110
of emotional and
psychological nourishment.

00:31:16.110 --> 00:31:18.390
Academically and
educationally, I still

00:31:18.390 --> 00:31:22.080
feel that we have
a long way to go,

00:31:22.080 --> 00:31:24.180
because so many more
things we have to do.

00:31:24.180 --> 00:31:27.020
And there are
constraints of HR there,

00:31:27.020 --> 00:31:30.250
like our location, why
that's far from the city.

00:31:30.250 --> 00:31:32.224
So there may be
concerns outside,

00:31:32.224 --> 00:31:33.390
and we'll grapple with that.

00:31:33.390 --> 00:31:37.250
But nothing stops us
from making Parivaar

00:31:37.250 --> 00:31:40.510
a very, very high degree of
emotionally nourishing place.

00:31:40.510 --> 00:31:42.870
So that has been the
case, right from day

00:31:42.870 --> 00:31:46.380
one when we were very,
very low on resources.

00:31:46.380 --> 00:31:48.380
So it's about the environment.

00:31:48.380 --> 00:31:54.800
So we have our own
[INAUDIBLE], working staff who

00:31:54.800 --> 00:31:56.580
actually stay on the campus.

00:31:56.580 --> 00:31:59.680
I have always lived
with the kids.

00:31:59.680 --> 00:32:01.285
That has been my family.

00:32:01.285 --> 00:32:03.635
So when I started,
I also decided

00:32:03.635 --> 00:32:06.670
that I will not have any
other thing in my life.

00:32:06.670 --> 00:32:09.060
So you know that
simplified my life.

00:32:09.060 --> 00:32:12.040
So as a result, I
never got married even.

00:32:12.040 --> 00:32:14.450
And my parents were
at some other place

00:32:14.450 --> 00:32:18.920
so didn't have much of a social
obligation outside Parivaar.

00:32:18.920 --> 00:32:20.930
So it was like this.

00:32:20.930 --> 00:32:24.270
So this has been my
family And for a tier

00:32:24.270 --> 00:32:27.260
of the resident people
who live at Parivaar

00:32:27.260 --> 00:32:28.480
and call it their family.

00:32:28.480 --> 00:32:33.790
And in addition, we have our
own 90 more daytime staff

00:32:33.790 --> 00:32:35.340
for our daytime roles.

00:32:35.340 --> 00:32:38.990
It could be teaching,
tutoring, all these things.

00:32:38.990 --> 00:32:40.200
So lots of things.

00:32:40.200 --> 00:32:47.410
You could say on fun and
joy and happiness quotient

00:32:47.410 --> 00:32:49.500
enhancements.

00:32:49.500 --> 00:32:51.970
So all the things
you can imagine

00:32:51.970 --> 00:32:56.275
which happen in a household--
celebrations, festivities,

00:32:56.275 --> 00:32:59.420
excursions, carnivals,
culturally--

00:32:59.420 --> 00:33:03.616
a huge amount of cultural
events, et cetera.

00:33:03.616 --> 00:33:05.880
Infrastructure-wise, right
from a rented building,

00:33:05.880 --> 00:33:08.600
then I, for the first
time, took to [INAUDIBLE].

00:33:08.600 --> 00:33:11.794
Now it became our own,
nearly 20 acres of land

00:33:11.794 --> 00:33:16.144
now and in two campuses.

00:33:16.144 --> 00:33:17.310
We have an immediate campus.

00:33:17.310 --> 00:33:20.499
One is for-- both are in
the same locality, actually,

00:33:20.499 --> 00:33:21.790
and are adjacent to each other.

00:33:21.790 --> 00:33:23.520
One is for the girls.

00:33:23.520 --> 00:33:28.170
And there, primarily, we have
our women resident staff.

00:33:28.170 --> 00:33:29.670
It's very, very
difficult, actually,

00:33:29.670 --> 00:33:32.850
to manage a girls'
residential home.

00:33:32.850 --> 00:33:35.350
And people would not
venture into doing that.

00:33:35.350 --> 00:33:37.825
There are very, very few
girls' residential institutions

00:33:37.825 --> 00:33:40.520
in India, whereas they
are the most vulnerable.

00:33:40.520 --> 00:33:43.490
Reason is that it's
very, very difficult

00:33:43.490 --> 00:33:47.200
to find resident women,
which you need for a girls'

00:33:47.200 --> 00:33:48.610
residential institute.

00:33:48.610 --> 00:33:51.810
You can get males who could
work in India on campus.

00:33:51.810 --> 00:33:52.592
They can stay.

00:33:52.592 --> 00:33:57.020
But usually our candidates
for having resident women

00:33:57.020 --> 00:34:00.240
is maybe women who are
not married, et cetera.

00:34:00.240 --> 00:34:03.703
I mean, the social
customs are maybe--

00:34:03.703 --> 00:34:07.984
in India it's usually like
married men can go out, get

00:34:07.984 --> 00:34:10.159
some other place,
and stay at resident

00:34:10.159 --> 00:34:12.960
or in overnight hall, but
very hard to find women.

00:34:12.960 --> 00:34:15.409
So that has always
been a constant.

00:34:15.409 --> 00:34:18.310
But right from the
beginning, I was

00:34:18.310 --> 00:34:23.920
dissuaded from actually
working and starting

00:34:23.920 --> 00:34:25.130
the girls' residentialship.

00:34:25.130 --> 00:34:26.505
Only women's social
entrepreneurs

00:34:26.505 --> 00:34:27.850
have done that mostly in India.

00:34:27.850 --> 00:34:31.679
But I was very, very sure,
right from the beginning that

00:34:31.679 --> 00:34:35.300
we'll have both girls'
institution as well as boys'.

00:34:35.300 --> 00:34:39.179
And we had a common residential
institution for at least

00:34:39.179 --> 00:34:40.699
first six, seven years.

00:34:40.699 --> 00:34:43.020
And after that only
we were in a position

00:34:43.020 --> 00:34:47.100
to have different institutions.

00:34:47.100 --> 00:34:49.580
Actually, having
common is, in fact,

00:34:49.580 --> 00:34:53.909
not-- some guidelines are
also there in the government,

00:34:53.909 --> 00:34:55.850
that you are not
allowed to do that.

00:34:55.850 --> 00:34:59.660
But somehow, we managed
to see that period.

00:34:59.660 --> 00:35:04.410
So these are some very wonderful
cases-- particularly these

00:35:04.410 --> 00:35:07.950
three, because these
three, after graduation,

00:35:07.950 --> 00:35:10.650
are also working at Parivaar.

00:35:10.650 --> 00:35:15.460
They chose to actually
give back for-- at least

00:35:15.460 --> 00:35:19.040
for the next three,
four years at Parivaar.

00:35:19.040 --> 00:35:20.970
So they are in very key roles.

00:35:20.970 --> 00:35:23.620
Firoz he was like-- 10
years back you can see.

00:35:23.620 --> 00:35:27.600
And now he's in an important
position in our finance

00:35:27.600 --> 00:35:29.560
accounting department.

00:35:29.560 --> 00:35:34.010
Suman now is looking after child
admissions administrative role.

00:35:34.010 --> 00:35:37.715
Ten years back, he, himself,
was a-- 11 years back

00:35:37.715 --> 00:35:40.190
got admitted to Parivaar.

00:35:40.190 --> 00:35:44.960
And Shubham, again, from a very
vulnerable, traffic-prone area.

00:35:44.960 --> 00:35:48.250
His sisters were
also-- well, you

00:35:48.250 --> 00:35:50.130
could say victims
of trafficking.

00:35:50.130 --> 00:35:52.640
And from there, he was-- all
the siblings were admitted.

00:35:52.640 --> 00:35:55.970
He's now a science teacher
in higher grades, mathematics

00:35:55.970 --> 00:35:59.010
and in the sciences.

00:35:59.010 --> 00:36:02.770
So this kind of a
spirit of-- actually

00:36:02.770 --> 00:36:05.550
there are many children who
are-- since they've come out

00:36:05.550 --> 00:36:08.480
of this system only, and
they carry this vision

00:36:08.480 --> 00:36:10.560
and philosophy of Parivaar.

00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:13.590
So I am very-- this
was my dream, actually,

00:36:13.590 --> 00:36:15.160
that the future
leaders of Parivaar

00:36:15.160 --> 00:36:18.740
should include in a major
way the children who

00:36:18.740 --> 00:36:21.750
have come through Parivaar.

00:36:21.750 --> 00:36:24.340
That was the legacy
I wanted to leave.

00:36:24.340 --> 00:36:27.420
So it's actually turning
out in that manner only.

00:36:27.420 --> 00:36:30.983
Now, in tribal areas
also we outreached

00:36:30.983 --> 00:36:34.960
and created a field network.

00:36:34.960 --> 00:36:37.280
In and around Kolkata,
our institution

00:36:37.280 --> 00:36:40.670
has become well known so
cases on their own come to us.

00:36:40.670 --> 00:36:43.420
But there are so many areas
which are almost cut off

00:36:43.420 --> 00:36:45.610
from the rest of the country.

00:36:45.610 --> 00:36:51.100
These are Naxal-affected
areas, and even police

00:36:51.100 --> 00:36:53.290
doesn't enter into these areas.

00:36:53.290 --> 00:36:56.525
So here, we actually outreach
created field network

00:36:56.525 --> 00:37:00.410
through local-- holding
community meetings.

00:37:00.410 --> 00:37:05.110
I remember in one Naxal
tribal area in 2007

00:37:05.110 --> 00:37:07.490
when during late evening
when nobody ventures

00:37:07.490 --> 00:37:10.000
because there are these mines.

00:37:10.000 --> 00:37:13.380
It's got mines, which are
placed and a bomb blast,

00:37:13.380 --> 00:37:14.790
kids get blasted there.

00:37:14.790 --> 00:37:17.740
So but still, we ventured there.

00:37:17.740 --> 00:37:21.290
And like in any random
interior village,

00:37:21.290 --> 00:37:25.250
I then brought-- the village
elders I brought to Parivaar.

00:37:25.250 --> 00:37:28.430
I said they'd be our
guest for, say, one week.

00:37:28.430 --> 00:37:32.830
And in every village, there are
some respected village elders.

00:37:32.830 --> 00:37:36.030
They are also from
the same community,

00:37:36.030 --> 00:37:38.550
but they are kind of opinion
leaders in that area.

00:37:38.550 --> 00:37:40.400
So we just brought them.

00:37:40.400 --> 00:37:42.910
And they stayed at
Parivaar and then went back

00:37:42.910 --> 00:37:44.170
and spread the word.

00:37:44.170 --> 00:37:45.750
So in areas where
nobody knew us,

00:37:45.750 --> 00:37:48.550
these kind of
approaches also we took.

00:37:48.550 --> 00:37:53.050
And then after that, all these
relatives of the children

00:37:53.050 --> 00:37:54.420
became our local volunteers.

00:37:54.420 --> 00:37:55.680
They are our field workers.

00:37:55.680 --> 00:37:59.170
We don't have recruited
staff for all that.

00:37:59.170 --> 00:38:02.579
All these relatives of the
children from far-flung area,

00:38:02.579 --> 00:38:04.120
they themselves are
a contact person.

00:38:04.120 --> 00:38:06.460
They do, then, the
primary referencing

00:38:06.460 --> 00:38:10.340
of more children in that
region, and all the liaisoning

00:38:10.340 --> 00:38:12.120
part with the area.

00:38:12.120 --> 00:38:14.320
These are two main
tribes-- [INAUDIBLE]

00:38:14.320 --> 00:38:16.620
and [INAUDIBLE] We do a
lot of other things here.

00:38:16.620 --> 00:38:19.000
Like around 3,000 other
children's education,

00:38:19.000 --> 00:38:21.540
we support through
various field groups which

00:38:21.540 --> 00:38:22.790
we have created in this field.

00:38:22.790 --> 00:38:25.940
And so this, Parivaar,
its main aspect

00:38:25.940 --> 00:38:29.240
is the residential instrument,
a lot of other ancillary support

00:38:29.240 --> 00:38:30.730
activity does.

00:38:30.730 --> 00:38:33.410
So 3,000 children's
education, we

00:38:33.410 --> 00:38:38.720
do a food stock scheme,
some 600, 700 households

00:38:38.720 --> 00:38:39.220
are covered.

00:38:39.220 --> 00:38:43.000
And around 15,000,
20,000 kilograms

00:38:43.000 --> 00:38:46.360
of [INAUDIBLE] every month
are fed into interior areas.

00:38:46.360 --> 00:38:49.060
These are starvation areas.

00:38:49.060 --> 00:38:51.775
And there are times when
there is a family in condition

00:38:51.775 --> 00:38:52.620
of starvation.

00:38:52.620 --> 00:38:55.020
Deaths even happen
in many such areas.

00:38:55.020 --> 00:38:57.060
So all this, also, we do.

00:38:57.060 --> 00:39:00.320
Since we are integrated
into those field areas.

00:39:00.320 --> 00:39:03.452
So these commitments,
also, we have to fulfill.

00:39:03.452 --> 00:39:09.370
Like here, it's [INAUDIBLE]
to additional 2,600 boys

00:39:09.370 --> 00:39:11.450
and all outside Parivaar
from this local area.

00:39:11.450 --> 00:39:15.810
Monthly food stock scheme--
this is for elderly.

00:39:15.810 --> 00:39:18.050
And there are other
families in the tribal area.

00:39:18.050 --> 00:39:19.470
But elderly are
uncared for women

00:39:19.470 --> 00:39:23.160
who are begging on the
streets, like that, with no one

00:39:23.160 --> 00:39:23.970
to take care of.

00:39:23.970 --> 00:39:29.850
So particularly, elderly uncared
women-- medical support, food

00:39:29.850 --> 00:39:31.920
stock support, and in
general Parivaar acts

00:39:31.920 --> 00:39:34.350
as a guardian of the
entire local area

00:39:34.350 --> 00:39:35.500
in case of any exigency.

00:39:35.500 --> 00:39:38.530
So ours is the
door they'll knock

00:39:38.530 --> 00:39:42.310
for any kind of
exigency support.

00:39:42.310 --> 00:39:44.800
Future-- this is how
we will be scaling.

00:39:44.800 --> 00:39:46.270
We may start a
similar institution

00:39:46.270 --> 00:39:48.400
in the next few
years, and possibly

00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:51.600
in Jharkhand, Madhya
Pradesh, or Chhattisgarh.

00:39:51.600 --> 00:39:53.630
These are also on our radar.

00:39:53.630 --> 00:39:55.200
But at the same
location, itself,

00:39:55.200 --> 00:39:57.260
we are scaling
three or four times.

00:39:57.260 --> 00:40:01.160
We have land, et cetera,
for 3,000, 4,000 children.

00:40:01.160 --> 00:40:03.436
So that will happen
at our area itself,

00:40:03.436 --> 00:40:07.870
present area with Bengal near
Kolkata, but at the same time

00:40:07.870 --> 00:40:12.010
in some other states where
we have a local village base.

00:40:12.010 --> 00:40:18.740
So finally speaking, Parivaar--
a continuous fest of joy

00:40:18.740 --> 00:40:19.320
and learning.

00:40:19.320 --> 00:40:21.710
This is what Parivaar is.

00:40:21.710 --> 00:40:25.040
And the central
government, particularly,

00:40:25.040 --> 00:40:27.740
has recognized our work--
government of India.

00:40:27.740 --> 00:40:32.850
And they've inducted me into
also-- three-fourths in point--

00:40:32.850 --> 00:40:34.300
the ministerial communities.

00:40:34.300 --> 00:40:37.620
Like I am on the
HRD's ministry, which

00:40:37.620 --> 00:40:40.160
is the education
ministry in India's apex

00:40:40.160 --> 00:40:44.030
advisory body for developing
the education policy.

00:40:44.030 --> 00:40:50.560
Similarly, in Ministry of Women
and Child, it's advisory board.

00:40:50.560 --> 00:40:53.590
In Ministry of
Finance, the aspect

00:40:53.590 --> 00:40:56.707
of finance ministry which deals
with NGOs in general, like they

00:40:56.707 --> 00:41:01.480
are taxation and regulations
which should guide the NGO

00:41:01.480 --> 00:41:03.830
sector, So all on that also.

00:41:03.830 --> 00:41:09.310
So it's like this--
a few years back

00:41:09.310 --> 00:41:11.420
Parivaar was elected
the best child welfare

00:41:11.420 --> 00:41:13.510
institution in
the entire country

00:41:13.510 --> 00:41:15.660
by the president of India.

00:41:15.660 --> 00:41:19.108
Now, these are just
a few tables, OPEX,

00:41:19.108 --> 00:41:24.590
and per child it comes to
around in Indian rupees

00:41:24.590 --> 00:41:27.570
be close to 440 rupees
annually per child,

00:41:27.570 --> 00:41:31.840
which is around US $650
US for a resident child.

00:41:31.840 --> 00:41:35.997
And you can see that nearly
half of it-- at least 40% to 45%

00:41:35.997 --> 00:41:37.330
is the funding component itself.

00:41:39.985 --> 00:41:42.440
So it's like this.

00:41:42.440 --> 00:41:48.970
And our OPEX it's around
Indian rupee crore,

00:41:48.970 --> 00:41:52.510
which now the exchange
rates have gone up already.

00:41:52.510 --> 00:41:56.250
So now it's around
US $800,000 a year.

