which is sort of unrelated,

00:48:06.446 --> 00:48:07.910
is how is the
government helping?

00:48:07.910 --> 00:48:10.600
Are you getting
help, positive help?

00:48:10.600 --> 00:48:11.100
Thank you.

00:48:11.100 --> 00:48:14.202
VINAYAK LOHANI: So I'll just
take the second part first.

00:48:14.202 --> 00:48:18.372
The government--
financial funding support

00:48:18.372 --> 00:48:21.280
from government in India
happens in a different way.

00:48:21.280 --> 00:48:23.660
Government has a number
of social welfare schemes.

00:48:23.660 --> 00:48:26.100
And if we run those
schemes directly

00:48:26.100 --> 00:48:30.300
under those parameters, in the
sense that you are kind of-- I

00:48:30.300 --> 00:48:33.020
would use the analogy of
being a subcontractor, so

00:48:33.020 --> 00:48:35.840
a subcontractor of
government schemes.

00:48:35.840 --> 00:48:39.190
If you run, then you
get those kind of funds.

00:48:39.190 --> 00:48:42.220
But in programs or
organizations or initiatives

00:48:42.220 --> 00:48:45.440
which have been designed, which
are not commissioned projects

00:48:45.440 --> 00:48:51.190
but are designed by some
entrepreneurs or founder

00:48:51.190 --> 00:48:55.400
and under your own design
parameter you want to do,

00:48:55.400 --> 00:48:58.650
then you don't have access
to those government funds.

00:48:58.650 --> 00:49:03.210
And even if you have, there is a
huge amount of loss of autonomy

00:49:03.210 --> 00:49:06.410
by taking government
funds in India.

00:49:06.410 --> 00:49:09.460
And government in
India is also--

00:49:09.460 --> 00:49:11.676
we have to understand
that there is

00:49:11.676 --> 00:49:13.050
a state government
in each state,

00:49:13.050 --> 00:49:15.180
and it's government of India.

00:49:15.180 --> 00:49:16.730
And usually, the
social way is you

00:49:16.730 --> 00:49:19.030
have to deal with the state
government, local state

00:49:19.030 --> 00:49:22.020
government, through channels
of local bureaucracy,

00:49:22.020 --> 00:49:25.250
local, say, panchayat system.

00:49:25.250 --> 00:49:29.440
There's a huge amount of
political interference there.

00:49:29.440 --> 00:49:34.080
So that's not--
when I started, I

00:49:34.080 --> 00:49:36.460
didn't think that
was an answer to go

00:49:36.460 --> 00:49:38.010
and building your organization.

00:49:38.010 --> 00:49:38.930
You lose control.

00:49:38.930 --> 00:49:40.930
But when you are in a
position of strength,

00:49:40.930 --> 00:49:43.937
then you can really
start dealing a bit more

00:49:43.937 --> 00:49:44.770
with the government.

00:49:44.770 --> 00:49:47.960
So now we are like-- some
kind of access we have.

00:49:47.960 --> 00:49:50.670
For example, there
is a provision

00:49:50.670 --> 00:49:53.400
of MPLAD for a member of
Parliament's local area

00:49:53.400 --> 00:49:53.960
development.

00:49:53.960 --> 00:49:57.590
So that doesn't come through
the ministerial departments,

00:49:57.590 --> 00:49:59.920
purely discretionary of
the member of Parliament.

00:49:59.920 --> 00:50:03.330
So a good member of
Parliament, there are a few,

00:50:03.330 --> 00:50:07.030
like-- I mean, particularly
in the Rajya Sabha, which is

00:50:07.030 --> 00:50:09.280
the House of Elders in India.

00:50:09.280 --> 00:50:11.320
And there are
president-nominated MPs there.

00:50:11.320 --> 00:50:14.170
So those are people who are
not from the political system.

00:50:14.170 --> 00:50:16.160
I mean, [INAUDIBLE]
was in their own field.

00:50:16.160 --> 00:50:19.310
So a few of them have
actually supported us.

00:50:19.310 --> 00:50:21.140
So there is also
government funding,

00:50:21.140 --> 00:50:23.940
where it doesn't come through
the conventional route.

00:50:23.940 --> 00:50:27.490
So about that, it's
a choice one has

00:50:27.490 --> 00:50:32.510
to make about loss of
autonomy and access to funds.

00:50:32.510 --> 00:50:35.130
Then about this, yeah.

00:50:35.130 --> 00:50:37.660
Your first part,
Parivaar is scaling up.

00:50:37.660 --> 00:50:43.340
So financial support would need
for that will always remain.

00:50:43.340 --> 00:50:45.670
But there are so many
other ways of engaging.

00:50:45.670 --> 00:50:48.770
Like from the US itself,
many of our supporters--

00:50:48.770 --> 00:50:52.770
for example, who have a
little bit more grown up kids.

00:50:52.770 --> 00:50:56.120
So we have a kid's exchange
program, for example.

00:50:56.120 --> 00:50:58.350
Not exchange-- their
kids, only come

00:50:58.350 --> 00:51:02.500
and staying for a
few weeks, and it's

00:51:02.500 --> 00:51:06.230
like-- living and sharing with.

00:51:06.230 --> 00:51:08.400
I don't use the
volunteering for that,

00:51:08.400 --> 00:51:10.030
but just living and sharing.

00:51:10.030 --> 00:51:13.630
So a lot of cross-cultural
learning for both our kids

00:51:13.630 --> 00:51:15.470
as well as those
who are visiting.

00:51:15.470 --> 00:51:20.210
That has been a very
successful thing at our end.

00:51:20.210 --> 00:51:24.140
So many diverse fields
of engagement are there.

00:51:24.140 --> 00:51:29.310
And as I said,
that I-- today I am

00:51:29.310 --> 00:51:33.800
representing not just in my
own work but sector as a whole.

00:51:33.800 --> 00:51:35.740
There are so many
other good initiatives.

00:51:35.740 --> 00:51:38.740
But right now, there is a
very, very divested thing,

00:51:38.740 --> 00:51:42.880
